cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper discusses the use of separable convolutions in deep convolutional neural network architectures, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also explores the underlying mechanism of action of separable convolutions, which could fall under the categories of neural networks (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and natural language processing (cs.CL) if the interpretation is applied to text data.
